    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1>Colors compare problem</h1>

<p>During my <a href="http://colorificapp.com">Colorific</a> development I found a problem - how to recognize that colors are similar. I've searched stack overflow and found some few algorythms which were useful but were not too helpful.</p>

<p>The very first idea was to measure distance in 3D (r,g,b) space between 2 colors:
$$
\sqrt{(R2 - R1)<sup>{2}</sup> + (G2-G1)<sup>{2}</sup> + (B2 - B1)<sup>{2}}</sup>
$$</p>

<p>Drawbacks
* No alpha support
* drawback 2
* drawback 3</p>

